UPSTREAM SOURCES
----------------
The AIRisk-2030 datasets are curated, harmonized, and re-aggregated from
publicly available upstream sources. Where applicable, we link each row in
each CSV to its original source via the `source` column. Major upstream
sources are:

  * METR — Task-horizon measurements (https://metr.org)
  * Epoch AI — Compute trends database (https://epochai.org)
  * Papers with Code — Benchmark leaderboards
  * Stanford HAI — AI Index annual reports
  * Partnership on AI — AI Incident Database (https://incidentdatabase.ai)
  * U.S. Bureau of Labor Statistics — Current Population Survey
  * OECD — Employment Outlook
  * IMF — World Economic Outlook
  * IEA — World Energy Outlook
  * USGS — Mineral Commodity Summaries
  * CSIS — Technology Competition Index reports
  * SIPRI — Defense R&D figures
  * World Bank — National accounts data

Users are responsible for honoring the upstream licenses of these sources
where they apply (most are public domain or permissive; consult each
source's terms for specifics).
